modules.description: Handles parsing and serialization of HTTP cookie date-time strings according to RFC 6265. Works with `Ptime.date` and `Ptime.time` tuples to represent moments in time. Used to convert between string representations in cookie headers and structured time values for validation or comparison.

This module parses and constructs HTTP cookie headers, handling cookie attributes like expiration, scope, security flags, and same-site policies. It works with string-based headers, structured cookie values, and time representations via `Ptime`. Concrete use cases include extracting cookies from request headers, preparing `Set-Cookie` headers for responses, and managing cookie expiration and domain scoping in web applications.
